icate. However, you must register with the Flemish government before you start working in the Flemish Region. This obligation applies to technicians who:</p><ul><li>obtained a European certificate outside the Flemish Region</li><li>have obtained a European certificate in the Flemish Region, but do not yet have a Flemish recognition certificate.</li></ul><p>If the European certificate is older than five years at the time of registration, the refrigeration technician must first pass the <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-de-koeltechnicus\">update exam at an accredited training centre</a> in order to obtain Flemish accreditation. </p><h2>Period of validity and obligations</h2><p>Recognition is valid for <strong>an indefinite</strong> period. However, as a recognised technician, you must fulfil some obligations.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-de-koeltechnicus\">More info on the obligations for accredited refrigeration technicians</a>.</p><p>The <strong>company </strong>for which the technician works must also have an <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-een-koeltechnisch-bedrijf\">accreditation as a refrigeration technician</a>.</p>","en":"<p>To be recognised as a refrigeration technician, you must fulfil:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> that apply to all recognitions relating to the environment<ul><li>in the 3 years that precede the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, the applicant has not been convicted of a criminal offence in a <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/en/working-enterprise-and-investment/the-countries-of-the-european-union-eu-the-european-economic-area-eea-the-schengen-area-and-the-eurozone\">member state of the European Economic Area</a>, for infringements of the environmental legislation concerning the use of the recognition.</li><li>in the 2 years that precede the application for